To make a decision on the cause of rotator cuff tears, the official in charge of the accident insurance depends on the medical expert. This paper deals with the etiology and pathogenesis of rotator cuff tears, with the possible influence of trauma and the varied causes of degenerative origin. All cases using expert opinion of the cause must take degenerative changes into consideration even if the patient was asymptomatic prior to the accident. The essential signs indicating previous damage to rotator cuff tendons can be seen in the first plain X-rays of the shoulder after the injury.  
